Among the students in Bukovina held a competition for the best computer program
54 participants took part in the final round of the competition

01 Nov 2019, 16:18

On October 30, 2019, the regional stage of the "Byte" competition for the best computer program among students of general secondary and extracurricular education was held.
The final round of the competition was attended by 54 participants - students of information technology circles of Chernivtsi Oblast Center for Scientific and Technical Creativity of Student Youth, City Center for Scientific and Technical Creativity of Student Youth, Chernivtsi National Team (Secondary School №3, №6, №24, №30 , # 41, gymnasium # 2), teams from Vyzhnytsia, Hlybotsky, Zatavnovsky, Novoselytsky, Putilsky, Sokyryansky, Khotyn, Kelmenetsky districts and Novodnistrovsk. About it reports the department of education and science of the Chernivtsi regional state administration.
Within the framework of the competition there were competitions in sections:

game programs - create animations using the graphical capabilities of Pascal and Scratch. Participants had to reproduce the graphic drawing and provide it with the given animation;
graphic editor Paint - play the proposed graphic drawing and color it at your own discretion;
training and demonstration programs - creating a presentation on "How to create a cartoon?"

According to the results of the jury, the certificates of the Department of Education and Science of Chernivtsi Regional State Administration were awarded for the 1st places:

in the Programming nomination:


Golecek Alexander - student of Chernivtsi secondary school ORT №41, head Freilichman G.Y .;
Alexander Streletsky - a student of the Slobidsky NVK, a pupil of the Novoselytskyi BDT, head of the Kolasko YS;
Nesin Andriy - pupil of gymnasium №2 in Chernivtsi, pupil of the circle of Chernivtsi regional center of scientific and technical creativity of student youth, head of Sporinina TT;


in the nomination "Training and demonstration programs":


Kulik Danylo - pupil of the Novodnistrovsk gymnasium of the Novodnistrovsk city council, head Moulyar ZI;


in the Paint Graphics Editor category:


Anastasia Bompa - pupil of gymnasium №2, Chernivtsi city, head Sporinina TT


